        <briefdescription>
<para>Get the time status at a given uptime. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Converts the device uptime (from <computeroutput>k_uptime_get</computeroutput>) to TAI time.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This function does not support status lookups for uptimes that occurred before the last received set- or status update. In addition, lookups for uptimes that happened before <computeroutput>k_uptime_get</computeroutput> must be used with caution, since there is no guarantee that the output data is fully reliable.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">srv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Time Server instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">uptime</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Uptime at the desired point in time. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">status</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The device&apos;s Time Status at the given uptime.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
